British No. 2 Dan Evans wants Aljaz Bedene’s bid to play for Great Britain in the Davis Cup blocked because he is already ‘capped’ for Slovenia.

Bedene, ranked 132 in the world, has lived in Britain since 2008 but represented Slovenia in three previous ties.

Evans, ranked 139, said: ‘He’s played Davis Cup for a different country so I just don’t think it would be right if he played Davis Cup for our country. It’s like in football, he’s already been capped for another country.

