British interest now lies with Murray and if his new coach Amelie Mauresmo needs any extra incentive to help him win Queen’s and defend his Wimbledon title, the comments of Australian Marinko Matosevic should do it.

‘For me, I couldn’t (have a female coach) since I don’t think that highly of the women’s game,’ he said.

‘But it’s all equal rights these days. Got to be politically correct.

‘So, yeah, someone’s got to give it a go but it won’t be me.’

